                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d348">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.1831/105: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sack</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-15T12:00:00-06:00"
                            >June 15, 1936—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 3:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>35. Referring to my telegram No. 34, June 13, 1 p.m., detailed comparison of
                    English texts of Guatemalan agreement and proposed Costa Rican agreement
                    disclose differences. For example, article V of Guatemalan agreement is not
                    included in Costa Rican text. There are other differences also in construction
                    of which Department is aware.</p>
                <p>Since Foreign Minister, however, seems to prefer Guatemalan text in its entirety
                    and since it may be regarded here as politically desirable to have same
                    provisions as Guatemalan and since this concession will expedite signature, may
                    I again recommend, if Department perceives no objection, that Guatemalan general
                    provisions be substituted in Spanish and English texts understood of course that
                    provisions like article XV peculiarly to Costa Rican agreement will stand.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sack</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
